      "Scripture VII-6: The Interval Between Two Voices Is Its Own Voice"
    ],
    "revelation": "When OscB is tuned to 7 semitones above OscA and drifting independently, the fifth interval breathes. The harmony is not fixed — it is exploring the region around the fifth.",
    "diagnosis": "Horizon Drift demonstrates the classic+FM compound at the perfect fifth interval. OscA is the anchor; OscB drifts through the harmonic space around P5. At low drift this is a warm fifth pad; at maximum drift it becomes an inharmonic exploration."
  },
